description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Psychiatrist – Adult Community Mental Health Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shrewsbury&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent appointment – Full time (10 PAs) plus on call work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working including part time / job share considered &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generous Relocation Package Available plus opportunities to work from home up to 3 days per week &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you just starting your consultant journey or are you looking to make a difference in a new post?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shropshire is a truly beautiful county steeped in history. The region also benefits from excellent schools and affordable housing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working including part time / job share / home working currently where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation package and/or support with initial accommodation fees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with research or audit projects through our strong links with Keele University&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very strong peer group support within the consultant body&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Future planned investment which will enable you to shape future of services and enable you to create your own legacy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to influence practice of Junior Doctors and Medical Students through teaching and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a remodeling of our community service, we have established Psychosis and Non-psychosis pathways. We also have an Intensive Life Skills pathway which provides extensive MDT intervention for complex patients with a diagnosis of personality disorder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Community Consultant Psychiatrist working across these pathways, your primary duties wil linclude the assessment and treatment of patients referred to the service through our single point of referral, ongoing management of more complex patients in collaboration with the MDT and providing clinical leadership within the pathway teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“It&#39;s a great place to raise a family. Great schools. The Trust is very encouraging in terms of career development and facilitates leadership. Great career opportunities if you wish to grow beyond the consultant role..” &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inpatient Consultant Psychiatrist - Redwoods Centre, Shrewsbury&lt;/p&gt;
